rules:
- id: rule-promotion-requires-evidence
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Pattern promotion to core must be supported by strong evidence, preferably
    from multiple sources or systems, to ensure core stability.
  title: Rule Promotion Requires Evidence
- id: rule-system-proposes-architect-decides
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All architectural decisions must be proposed by the system and explicitly
    accepted, rejected, or deferred by an architect to maintain human-in-the-loop
    control.
  title: Rule System Proposes Architect Decides
- id: rule-heuristic-patterns-require-signals
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All heuristic-derived patterns must include at least one linked signal
    as evidence to ensure traceability and grounding in observed behavior.
  title: Rule Heuristic Patterns Require Signals
- id: rule-workflow-execution-model-compliance
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All runtime-native workflows must conform to the CAS Workflow Execution
    Model, maintaining separation between orchestration (Runner), reasoning (Workflow),
    and knowledge access.
  title: Rule Workflow Execution Model Compliance
- compliance:
    enabled: true
  id: rule-adr-single-source-of-truth
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Architecture decisions must be recorded and updated only in ADRs; all other
    representations (AEM, metadata) must be derived from them.
  title: Rule Adr Single Source Of Truth
- id: rule-precedence-hierarchy
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: 'Defines the precedence order for rule resolution: Global Rules > Project
    Rules > Prompt Rules. Global rules act as hard constraints.'
  title: Rule Precedence Hierarchy
- id: rule-decision-status-drives-stage
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: The lifecycle stage of any architecture item (NEXT, DONE, FUTURE) must
    be derived from its decision status (proposed, accepted, deferred).
  title: Rule Decision Status Drives Stage
- id: rule-architecture-work-authority
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Architecture Work is the authoritative source for planning state; generated
    artifacts like AEM and AID must derive status from it.
  title: Rule Architecture Work Authority
- id: rule-generated-artifacts-not-authoritative
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Generated governance artifacts must summarize authoritative sources and
    must not become the source of truth themselves.
  title: Rule Generated Artifacts Not Authoritative
- id: rule-do-not-merge-across-architectural-layers
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Patterns must not be merged or consolidated across different architectural
    layers to preserve clarity between governance, execution, and contracts.
  title: Rule Do Not Merge Across Architectural Layers
- id: rule-aem-consistency-with-decisions
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: The Architecture Evolution Map (AEM) must reflect and never contradict
    Architecture Decision Records (ADR).
  title: Rule Aem Consistency With Decisions
- id: rule-decisions-must-be-persisted
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All architectural decisions must be persisted as structured ADRs before
    being reflected in AEM or other artifacts.
  title: Rule Decisions Must Be Persisted
- id: rule-core-patterns-must-be-foundational
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Core patterns must represent foundational architectural primitives rather
    than specific implementation strategies.
  title: Rule Core Patterns Must Be Foundational
- id: rule-language-semantic-contract
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Defines the semantic contract for architecture language, distinguishing
    between intent and state, and standardizing lifecycle terminology.
  title: Rule Language Semantic Contract
- compliance:
    enabled: true
  id: rule-decision-schema-must-be-structured
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All decisions must be expressed using a specific structured YAML decision
    schema to enable machine processing and consistency.
  title: Rule Decision Schema Must Be Structured
- id: rule-patterns-born-as-supporting
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All patterns must be created as supporting by default and validated through
    evidence before promotion to core.
  title: Rule Patterns Born As Supporting
- id: rule-shared-knowledge-workspace
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Projects must participate in the shared Knowledge Workspace and avoid duplicating
    existing global governance structures.
  title: Rule Shared Knowledge Workspace
- compliance:
    enabled: true
  id: rule-pattern-decision-lifecycle-alignment
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Ensures consistent interpretation between pattern maturity (knowledge evolution)
    and decision status (governance lifecycle).
  title: Rule Pattern Decision Lifecycle Alignment
- id: rule-signal-promotion-criteria
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Signals are promoted to patterns only if they meet recurrence, impact,
    reusability, and stability criteria supported by observable evidence.
  title: Rule Signal Promotion Criteria
summary:
  global_rules: 19
  project_rules: 0
  total_rules: 19
